{"staticAdditionalInfo":"<p>Hercule III-funded actions aim <strong>to protect the financial interests of the European Union <u>by preventing and combating</u> </strong>fraud, corruption and any other illegal activities affecting the financial interests of the Union.</p><p>The Commission will encourage actions that are jointly undertaken by the Programme's beneficiaries in different Member States to provide technical assistance in order to strengthen cross-border cooperation to fight activities detrimental to the Union's financial interests, such as smuggling of tobacco, cigarettes or VAT-carousels.</p><p><strong>Maximum project duration</strong>: 18 months</p>
<p> </p><p>The indicative available budget for grants for this Call is <strong>EUR 9 866 200</strong>.</p><p>The grants will cover a maximum of <strong>80%</strong> (<strong>90% in exceptional </strong>and duly justified cases ) of the eligible costs of the action.</p><p>The minimum threshold for the TOTAL budgeted costs of a project submitted is set at <strong>EUR 100 000</strong>. Therefore, the REQUESTED GRANT for the action must be at least <strong>EUR 80 000</strong> (80% of EUR 100 000).</p>
"}

